ratings.comment: Brayden is a rare professor who makes learning both effective and enjoyable. He's sharp, engaging, and has a great sense of humor that keeps the class interesting. He explains concepts in a way that makes them easy to understand and is always willing to help. Definitely take this class from him

Brayden is a great instructor who makes accounting both understandable and enjoyable. He's incredibly knowledgeable, explains concepts clearly, and brings a great sense of humor to his teaching. His approachable and supportive nature makes it easy to ask questions, and he genuinely wants his students to succeed. Great guy!

Brayden is an amazing accounting professor! He's incredibly knowledgeable, explains concepts clearly, and truly cares about his students' success. He's always approachable, easy to talk to, and willing to help when you need it. His passion for teaching makes learning accounting so much easier. Highly recommend this class!

This was Brayden's first time teaching a master's class, but it was great. Be prepared to work and study, but his grading is fair and expectations are super clear. If you meet with him and ask questions, you will do amazing. He gives his students so much time and is available to offer help. I would definitely have gone to more office hours.
Brayden is great. You can tell he really cares about his students and he really knows his stuff.
